{{Quote|All those years aboard the ''Axe'', apprentice, and you still don't get it&mdash;the only ''true'' loyalty is to ''yourself''. All other loyalties are for ''rent'' or ''sale''. That's why you'll always be ''owned'', Syn.|Rav, to Jariah Syn|<ref name="Legacy 3" />}}
'''Rav''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Feeorin/Legends|Feeorin]] [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] who was the owner of a bounty clearing house and [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]], the [[Golden Gorg Cantina|Golden Gorg]], during the era of the [[Sith–Imperial War]] and the [[Second Imperial Civil War]]. He was also a collaborator to the [[One Sith]] and [[Darth Krayt]]'s [[Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire|Galactic Empire]]. His pirate symbol, the [[Bloody Bones (insignia)|Bloody Bones]], was feared across [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].

==Biography==
During a raid on [[Roon/Legends|Roon]] for fun, Rav and [[Zareb Syn]] were attacked by [[Rasi Tuum]], a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] who was trying to defend a mining camp. Rav lost his leg to Tuum's [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] during the encounter. Zareb tried to kill the Jedi only to be killed himself in front of his son, [[Jariah Syn|Jariah]]. Rav twisted the events to the young boy, telling him that he and his father were simply trading when the Jedi attacked without provocation. He also claimed that the young [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanian]] girl next to them was going to be stolen away to the Order, when in reality, she was just a prisoner. Rav later got a mechanical leg to replace the one he lost.

Rav owed some form of debt to Zareb, and as a result took Jariah into his crew. In the aftermath of the [[Massacre at Ossus|Massacre of Ossus]] in [[130 ABY]], he took [[Cade Skywalker]] aboard the [[Crimson Axe]] as his apprentice on the request of Jariah, with Cade hiding his [[Skywalker family/Legends|famous lineage]] or role as a Jedi [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]]. He and his crew raided the [[Jedi Praxeum]] on Ossus, finding the corpses leftover from the attack. He laughed at the bodies, joking that Jedi just die. He had a cross-shaped scar running over one eye, and his right leg was mechanical from the knee down, with weapons supposedly hidden within it. For seven years, Rav trained Cade in the "free" way and had him swear the [[Bloody Bones oath]]. He later retired from pirating and opened a bounty clearing house on [[Socorro/Legends|Socorro]]. Here, Rav provided the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] numerous services, including ship repairs. He was also a [[Spice/Legends|spice]] runner, and used this to keep addicted bounty hunters (such as Skywalker) in his debt. Rav frequently spoke [[Huttese/Legends|Huttese]].

When Cade and his crew came to Socorro to cash in the bounties on bond-skipper [[Naxy Screeger]] and the Jedi [[Hosk Trey'lis]] in [[137 ABY]], he gave Skywalker three [[Death stick/Legends|death sticks]] on credit, enraging Jariah Syn, who wished to be out of Rav's debt. One of his henchmen escorted Naxy away and the other, a [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]], carried Trey'lis off. He lectured Syn that one's loyalty is to self and that he would always be owned.

Rav later double-crossed Syn and Blue by turning them into the [[Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[Director of Imperial Intelligence|Director]] of [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Intelligence]], [[Morrigan Corde|Nyna Calixte]], for harboring Cade, whom he had just found out was a Jedi.
[[File:Naxy.jpg|thumb|left|[[Naxy Screeger]] turned over to Rav.]]
He was later tracked down by Cade, Syn, [[Chak (Wookiee)|Chak]] and [[Kee]] because he had Chak's ship, the ''[[Grinning Liar]]''. After a brief fight, which Cade and his friends won, Rav reluctantly returned the ship to Chak and Kee and swore his own oath to Skywalker. He later reported to [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lady]] [[Darth Maladi]], the head of [[Sith Intelligence and Assassination]], swearing his oath to her and promising to deliver any information concerning his former protegé.

Under Lady Maladi's orders, Rav hired the crew of the ''Mynock'' for a job on the planet [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]], a job he referred as a simple "[[Blue milk run/Legends|blue milk run]]." However, it was a [[Wayland trap|trap]] set up by Lady Maladi and Rav to capture Skywalker.

==Behind the scenes==
[[John Ostrander]] considered calling him the "Dread Pirate Rav" as a nod to [[Wikipedia:Dread Pirate Roberts|Dread Pirate Roberts]] from [[Wikipedia:The Princess Bride|''The Princess Bride'']], but decided against it, as Rav was "NOTHING like ANY" of the characters from that movie.

